      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum mechanics constitutive model (isotropic hardening plasticity) appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V; contact formulation captures screw-rod interface behavior observed experimentally.",
      "rationale": "The pedicle screw and rod are modeled using isotropic hardening plasticity (Ramberg-Osgood) calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V tensile coupon data. Augmented Lagrangian contact at the screw-rod and screw-block interfaces captures the frictional slip observed in bench testing. Model form is consistent with ASTM F1717 loading mode. Gradation 3 achieved."
